                            <comment id="14512019" author="stack" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2015 23:33:18 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Could we have a timeout on servers that are not alive?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These are supposed to get cleaned up... we going a code path not considered previously?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14512029" author="eclark" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2015 23:41:10 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;These are supposed to get cleaned up... we going a code path not considered previously?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not completely sure. This was a a freak accident on a production cluster. I&apos;ll try and reproduce on a test cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14605181" author="vik.karma" created="Mon, 29 Jun 2015 06:11:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have seen this happen few times when all the DataNodes holding the primary and replicated copies of the corresponding HBase datafiles go down and are brought back up. Might help in reproducing the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
